  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.17.3\n\n### What happened?\n\nIn delegatecall, target contract state variables are incorrect when doing unit test.\r\nHere is a simplified version of smart contract for reproduction.\r\n````\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\n\r\nimport \"hardhat/console.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract Foo {\r\n  address public masterChef;\r\n  \r\n  constructor() {\r\n    masterChef = address(0x9BA666165867E916Ee7Ed3a3aE6C19415C2fBDDD);\r\n  }\r\n  \r\n  function stake() external view {\r\n    console.log(masterChef);\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract Test {\r\n  address strategy;\r\n\r\n  function setStrategy(address _strategy) external {\r\n    strategy = _strategy;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  function callStrategy() public {\r\n    bytes memory performData = abi.encodeWithSignature(\"stake()\");\r\n    (bool success, ) = strategy.delegatecall(performData);\r\n    require(success == true, \"delegatecall failed\");\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\n````\r\nAnd this is a test file in javascript.\r\n````\r\n\r\ndescribe(\"test\", function () {\r\n  it(\"test\", async function () {\r\n    const foo = await ethers.deployContract(\"Foo\");\r\n    const test = await ethers.deployContract(\"Test\");\r\n    \r\n    await test.setStrategy(foo.target);\r\n\r\n    await test.callStrategy();\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n````\r\nIt should print the masterchef address i hardcoded but see different address(it seems the deployed address of foo contract).\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\nJust run `npx hardhat test` with the above the code.\n\n### Search terms\n\ndelegatecall",
