    "body": "That behavior is correct, unless I'm missing something.\r\n\r\nThe way delegate call works is that the storage of the *calling* contract will be used with the logic of the *called* contract. In this case, the logic says \"log the first address in the storage\", but since the storage of `Test` is being used for that, you get a log with the `strategy` address.\r\n\r\nTentatively closing because I think this is working as expected.",
